SP  - 1652
EP  - 1669
VL  - 36
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Measures of strategy made at the product and business level were compared using data from a large multiproduct U.S. firm. The business-level results were not found to be good indicators of product-level strategies. Also, contrary to previous research, no evidence of the use of combined cost-leadership and differentiation strategies was found at the product level.
AB  - Measures of strategy made at the product and business level were compared using data from a large multiproduct U.S. firm. The business-level results were not found to be good indicators of product-level strategies. Also, contrary to previous research, no evidence of the use of combined cost-leadership and differentiation strategies was found at the product level.
